olive oil
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 onion
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 cucumber
½ lemon
1 bag Rocket leaves
2 brioche hotdog buns
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Corn Chips
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Finely chop chorizo. Thinly slice
onion
• Heat frying pan over medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
chorizo and onion, tossing, until
browned, 5-6 mins
• Remove from heat and stir through
onion chutney

• Thinly slice cucumber. Halve lemon
• In a bowl, combine rocket, a squeeze
of lemon juice and a drizzle of oil.
Season

• Halve buns and toast or grill to your
liking
• Spread buns with some aioli, then
top with cucumber, rocket, chorizo
and cheese
• Serve with corn chips and remaining
rocket